data.text:
Established in 1983, a year after Philip K Dick's Death, the Philip K Dick Award is awarded to the best original paperback book published each year in the USA.

Presented here is a complete list of the award winners, the date indicates the year the award was actually decided and presented, the book was published in the previous year. 1989 and 2009 show two entries as both years there way a tied decision.

Winners are listed next to the year while nominees are listed below in grey.
